l,"comments":4,"created_at":"2020-09-15T19:09:45Z","updated_at":"2020-10-05T19:28:16Z","closed_at":"2020-10-05T19:28:16Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"Graspy and topologic have divergent systems regarding materialization of the version number prior to publication.\r\n\r\nTopologic publishes dev versions (e.g. 0.1.0dev123456789) to [PyPI](https://pypi.org/) on each merge to a dev branch so that they can be tested (and documentation verified) prior to a full release.  This is done automatically based on the [semver](https://semver.org/) provided in a file and the merge to the develop branch.\r\n\r\nUpon merge into main, the `dev123456789` is dropped and an actual `0.1.0` version is published to pypi.org.\r\n\r\nFrom what I can tell, Graspy's version is updated manually, and I actually am not sure how publish occurs - @bdpedigo, can you shed some light on the current process?\r\n\r\nRegardless, it's not a bad idea to publish our pre-releases as long as they're clearly defined as pre-releases, and we also want to minimize the manual steps required in favor of CICD just to minimize the human element (namely, the human element of forgetting to do something).","closed_by":{"login":"daxpryce","id":899411,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg5OTQxMQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/899411?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/daxpryce","html_url":"https://github.com/daxpryce","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daxpryce/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daxpryce/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daxpryce/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daxpryce/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daxpryce/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daxpryce/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daxpryce/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daxpryce/ev